  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\n\r\nIf I create a community and add permission for becoming an `admin` and invite a mobile user there who does not have the required tokens, then the community will look like a `token-gated` one for them, although no permissions were added for becoming a `member`. \r\n\r\nCommunity permissions:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1121\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-01-15 at 12 29 34\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/67952253/200062cb-a1a4-4e67-9b9c-33c97ea31df4\">\r\n\r\nWhat the mobile user (who does not have the required tokens) sees when opening this community:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<img width=\"363\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-01-15 at 12 28 28\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/67952253/f662804d-7f47-4400-a85a-26bd099ef546\">\r\n\r\n<img width=\"361\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-01-15 at 12 29 03\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/67952253/c816691b-f686-4750-8481-e0cde8944da7\">\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe community looks like a not-token-gated one for such users\r\n\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/h9wo4GipgZURbqqr1vShFN/Communities-for-Mobile?type=design&node-id=15331-284611&mode=design&t=g70SAiz9D6OgM1VU-4\r\n\r\n<img width=\"365\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-01-15 at 12 32 29\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/67952253/6733fbb6-efde-4882-a45f-a622aa01f3ce\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n**Desktop user:**\r\n1. Create a community on desktop\r\n2. Go to community settings > `Permissions` > `Add new permission`\r\n3. Select any token (the mobile user **should not** have this token)\r\n4. In `Is allowed to` select `Become an admin`\r\n5. Click `Create permission` \r\n6. Add Mobile user to contacts and invite them to the community\r\n\r\n**Mobile user:**\r\n1. Open the community from the invite\r\n2. Check the community page\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status mobile version: nightly 15/01\r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n- Status desktop version: 0.15.0 https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/releases/tag/0.15.0\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Note\r\n\r\nThis case is also relevant for communities with a minted Owner token:\r\n\r\nif you create a community and mint Owner token there, it'll \"become\" (will look like) a token-gated community for any user.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce will be:\r\n**Desktop user:**\r\n1. Create a community on desktop\r\n2. Go to community settings > `Tokens` > `Mint Owner token`\r\n3. Do not add any permissions manually\r\n4. Invite Mobile user to the community\r\n\r\n**Mobile user:**\r\n1. Open the community from the invite\r\n2. Check the community page\r\n\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1404\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-01-15 at 12 41 57\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/67952253/9fd076f8-8fd0-4905-a1f9-d19e0408d06d\">\r\n\r\nMentioning this case here to make sure it'll be covered when fixing the issue. ",
